The paper discusses the use of depth sensing for automation of surgical subtasks using the da Vinci Research Kit (dVRK), which is a robotic system used for surgical procedures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses calibration techniques and explores the potential of depth sensing, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The study also reports experimental results, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
